series.name: Goldilocks and The Three Bears
series.premise: A lost girl unknowingly enters a bear's home
series.theme: Consider how your actions affect others

children.text: Very tired, Goldilocks goes upstairs to the bedroom...
The first bed is too hard.
The second bed is too soft.
The third bed is just right!
And then she falls asleep.
Tired, Golidocks decides to sit on a chair...
The first chair is too big.
The second chair is also too big.
The third (and smallest) chair is just right!
But as she sits on the chair, it breaks into pieces.
The first bowl is too hot.
The second bowl is too cold.
The third bowl is just right!
She runs out the door, into the forest.
She sees the bears, screams for help, and runs out of the room.
They are not pleased by what they discover.
Goldilocks is hungry.
She knocks on the door and walks right in when nobody answers.
Three bears
Three bowls of porridge
Three chairs
Three beds
Three indiscretions
The bears leave their door unlocked, trusting no one will enter.
Goldilocks breaks their trust and runs away before she has to suffer repercussions.
Strangers can be dangerous:
Goldilocks (a stranger) entered and caused damaged to the bears' home.
Goldilocks could be seriously harmed if the bears (strangers to her) find her.
Goldilocks invites herself into their house, disrespecting the bears' space.
Furthermore, she invites herself to their food and furniture.
